25 or 50 cents, I don't know, whatever.

00:13:23.360 --> 00:13:24.950
But it's a good read:

00:13:24.960 --> 00:13:27.190
In Him by Kenneth E. Hagin.

00:13:27.200 --> 00:13:29.390
Little short book, 32 pages.

00:13:29.400 --> 00:13:30.790
Pretty cool, huh?

00:13:30.800 --> 00:13:32.110
I like stuff like that; it's like a

00:13:32.120 --> 00:13:33.990
little

00:13:33.990 --> 00:13:34.000
pocketbook.

00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:35.870
Diana found that for me.

00:13:35.880 --> 00:13:37.870
I told her, 'Thanks,

00:13:37.870 --> 00:13:37.880
baby.'She

00:13:37.880 --> 00:13:39.350
got that and said, 'Hey, Brandon, I

00:13:39.360 --> 00:13:41.110
think you need to read this: In

00:13:41.110 --> 00:13:41.120
Him.'I

00:13:41.120 --> 00:13:43.030
have some more over

00:13:43.040 --> 00:13:44.870
there. Braden, will you get those other

00:13:44.880 --> 00:13:48.230
two little books mama got me

00:13:48.240 --> 00:13:51.310
over there?

00:13:51.320 --> 00:13:53.150
If Diana was here, she could read

00:13:53.160 --> 00:13:55.430
this to you in less than five minutes.

00:13:55.440 --> 00:13:58.030
She's a fast reader. Oh, she got me

00:13:58.040 --> 00:14:00.390
