00:14:29.040 --> 00:14:32.230
it has 71 pages in that one.

00:14:32.240 --> 00:14:34.470
So, it's a pretty cool little book she

00:14:34.480 --> 00:14:35.510
got me.

00:14:35.520 --> 00:14:37.110
It came in the mail;

00:14:37.120 --> 00:14:39.270
she got it from Amazon, I guess.

00:14:39.280 --> 00:14:40.710
She surprised me and said,

00:14:40.720 --> 00:14:42.790
'Hey, I got that for you tonight. Look

00:14:42.800 --> 00:14:45.590
what I got you,

00:14:45.590 --> 00:14:45.600
Braden—Brandon.'So

00:14:45.600 --> 00:14:48.069
I'll share with Brent, my son. He

00:14:48.079 --> 00:14:51.230
can read one, and I'll read one a day.

00:14:51.240 --> 00:14:53.829
It keeps you stirred up. You

00:14:53.829 --> 00:14:53.839
have

00:14:53.839 --> 00:14:55.870
to fan that

00:14:55.880 --> 00:14:57.110
flame.

00:14:57.120 --> 00:15:00.910
You cannot let your flame go down in these last days.

00:15:13.480 --> 00:15:16.350
You have to stir yourself up. And that's

00:15:16.360 --> 00:15:18.069
what I'm trying to tell you. This is

00:15:18.079 --> 00:15:20.030
how I do it. This is how Diana does it. She'll

00:15:20.040 --> 00:15:21.110
read one of these little books, she'll

00:15:21.120 --> 00:15:22.390
drive around and

00:15:22.390 --> 00:15:22.400
say,

00:15:22.400 --> 00:15:25.150
'Let's read that,'finding things

00:15:25.160 --> 00:15:27.030
to keep yourself stirred up in

00:15:27.040 --> 00:15:28.790
these last days.

00:15:28.800 --> 00:15:31.230
Don't wait on your pastor to feed you.

00:15:31.240 --> 00:15:32.870
Don't wait on the evangelist to feed

00:15:32.880 --> 00:15:34.110
you. Don't wait on a prophet to feed

00:15:34.120 --> 00:15:36.150
you. Don't wait on YouTube to feed you.

00:15:36.160 --> 00:15:40.270
You have to be a scavenger. How

00:15:40.270 --> 00:15:40.280
badly

00:15:40.280 --> 00:15:42.910
do you want your life to change?

00:15:42.920 --> 00:15:45.630
How desperate are you to find stuff?

00:15:45.640 --> 00:15:46.990
That's why we're always looking

00:15:47.000 --> 00:15:48.270
for stuff.

00:15:48.280 --> 00:15:50.590
My goodness,

00:15:50.600 --> 00:15:53.030
if I waited on my pastors to feed me

00:15:53.040 --> 00:15:54.949
only, you would

00:15:54.959 --> 00:15:56.390
die spiritually. Do you understand? You

00:15:56.400 --> 00:15:58.990
can't wait on people.

00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:01.270
You have to

00:16:01.280 --> 00:16:03.710
be a contender. The Lord said, 'Brandon,

00:16:03.720 --> 00:16:07.270
I'm putting my closers

00:16:07.270 --> 00:16:07.280
in.'He

00:16:07.280 --> 00:16:09.030
said, 'I've saved the best for last—my

00:16:09.030 --> 00:16:09.040
closers.'Diana

00:16:09.040 --> 00:16:11.150
and

00:16:11.150 --> 00:16:11.160
I

00:16:11.160 --> 00:16:13.150
started doing

00:16:13.160 --> 00:16:15.350
research on the closers; they

00:16:15.350 --> 00:16:15.360
are

00:16:15.360 --> 00:16:20.110
built for pressure.

00:16:20.120 --> 00:16:23.470
Closers in baseball—the ones that close the baseball

00:16:23.470 --> 00:16:23.480
game—are

00:16:23.480 --> 00:16:25.710
built for

00:16:25.720 --> 00:16:28.230
pressure. They don't lose the lead

00:16:28.240 --> 00:16:29.750
because they're not going, 'Oh

00:16:29.750 --> 00:16:29.760
gosh.'You

00:16:29.760 --> 00:16:31.510
know

00:16:31.510 --> 00:16:31.520
about

00:16:31.520 --> 00:16:33.870
buck fever

00:16:33.870 --> 00:16:33.880
when

00:16:33.880 --> 00:16:35.550
you're hunters and you're out there and

00:16:36.880 --> 00:16:39.470
your hands are shaking from the pressure

00:16:39.480 --> 00:16:41.270
of the buck walking in front of

00:16:41.280 --> 00:16:43.030
you. You miss the shot because

00:16:43.030 --> 00:16:43.040
you've

00:16:43.040 --> 00:16:44.510
got buck fever.

00:16:48.160 --> 00:16:49.949
That's where we are in these end times.

00:16:49.959 --> 00:16:52.550
God made us for pressure. He said,

00:16:52.560 --> 00:16:54.790
'Brandon, we've got this,

00:16:54.800 --> 00:16:56.910
but you've got to be a contender. You can't

00:16:56.920 --> 00:16:58.430
just sit there and lay down on the job

00:16:58.440 --> 00:17:01.270
and say,

00:17:01.270 --> 00:17:01.280
"Stop."'Nobody

00:17:01.280 --> 00:17:03.550
feels sorry for you. That's

00:17:03.560 --> 00:17:04.829
what the Lord said. Nobody feels sorry

00:17:04.839 --> 00:17:06.110
for you.

00:17:06.120 --> 00:17:08.630
Do you understand?

00:17:08.630 --> 00:17:08.640
You've

00:17:08.640 --> 00:17:10.189
got to play the world's smallest

00:17:10.199 --> 00:17:12.470
violin for

00:17:12.470 --> 00:17:12.480
yourself?

00:17:12.480 --> 00:17:15.470
'You had a hard day. The enemy

00:17:15.480 --> 00:17:18.069
was attacking.'Stand up and fight.

00:17:18.079 --> 00:17:20.310
Be a contender. Say, 'No, I'm not

00:17:20.320 --> 00:17:22.150
going to let you do this.

00:17:22.160 --> 00:17:23.710
I'm not going to let you rob my family

00:17:23.720 --> 00:17:25.350
of finances. I'm not going to let you

00:17:25.360 --> 00:17:27.230
rob me of health.

00:17:27.240 --> 00:17:28.630
I'm not

00:17:28.640 --> 00:17:30.750
going to sit here and have a snotty nose

00:17:30.760 --> 00:17:32.270
and have all this going on with me.

00:17:32.280 --> 00:17:35.910
I refuse to do

00:17:35.920 --> 00:17:39.350
this. I have a covenant with

00:17:39.350 --> 00:17:39.360
God.'You

00:17:39.360 --> 00:17:41.350
either are or you aren't. Are

00:17:41.350 --> 00:17:41.360
you

00:17:41.360 --> 00:17:42.750
a believing believer

00:17:42.760 --> 00:17:44.510
or not?

00:17:44.520 --> 00:17:46.630
Are we believing believers in these last

00:17:46.630 --> 00:17:46.640
days

00:17:46.640 --> 00:17:49.710
or are we not?

00:17:49.720 --> 00:17:51.230
That's why I started saying, 'I'm done

00:17:51.240 --> 00:17:54.270
with

00:17:54.270 --> 00:17:54.280
this.'When

00:17:54.280 --> 00:17:55.550
you say you're barely getting

00:17:55.560 --> 00:17:58.070
by, or

00:17:58.070 --> 00:17:58.080
you're

00:17:58.080 --> 00:18:00.590
done not feeling good... 'Oh,

00:18:00.600 --> 00:18:02.110
you're overweight.'Well, you eat too

00:18:02.120 --> 00:18:05.830
much.

00:18:10.000 --> 00:18:11.710
I work on myself daily.

00:18:13.120 --> 00:18:14.750
'Well, you feel sorry for

00:18:14.750 --> 00:18:14.760
yourself.'No,

00:18:14.760 --> 00:18:16.350
you're the one that put the food in

00:18:16.360 --> 00:18:18.430
there.

00:18:18.430 --> 00:18:18.440
You've

00:18:18.440 --> 00:18:20.790
got one hole;

00:18:20.800 --> 00:18:21.990
you don't have to keep putting

00:18:22.000 --> 00:18:24.630
food in it all day long.

00:18:26.360 --> 00:18:28.190
The Lord gets on me about a

00:18:28.200 --> 00:18:31.190
lot of stuff. I walk a very

00:18:31.190 --> 00:18:31.200
tightrope

00:18:31.200 --> 00:18:33.310
with the Father.

00:18:33.320 --> 00:18:35.350
He's instructed me on what

00:18:35.360 --> 00:18:37.070
I'm supposed to be doing with my life,

00:18:37.080 --> 00:18:38.270
telling me, 'This is how you get

00:18:39.470 --> 00:18:39.480
there.'He

00:18:41.280 --> 00:18:42.990
always said, 'Brandon, if you

00:18:43.000 --> 00:18:44.110
want change in your life, you're going

00:18:44.120 --> 00:18:45.630
to have to change the way you're doing

00:18:45.640 --> 00:18:47.470
things because you can't keep doing the

00:18:47.480 --> 00:18:52.110
same thing expecting different results.

00:18:52.120 --> 00:18:54.030
How badly do you want to go on with

00:18:54.040 --> 00:18:56.669
me? How badly do you want

00:18:56.669 --> 00:18:56.679
this?'You

00:18:56.679 --> 00:18:59.790
want impartation from these generals?

00:18:59.800 --> 00:19:01.909
You want impartation, but are you a

00:19:01.919 --> 00:19:03.990
contender for it? Do you do what they

00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:06.669
did to get it—from Billy

00:19:06.669 --> 00:19:06.679
Burke

00:19:06.679 --> 00:19:09.310
to

00:19:09.310 --> 00:19:09.320
Lynne

00:19:09.320 --> 00:19:11.390
Hammond

00:19:11.390 --> 00:19:11.400
to

00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:14.190
whoever you know has been

00:19:14.200 --> 00:19:18.149
in ministry for 50 or 60 years? Do you do

00:19:18.159 --> 00:19:22.750
what they did to get where they are?

00:19:22.760 --> 00:19:24.270
They've sustained it and they've

00:19:24.280 --> 00:19:25.710
been there. Or do you just sit there and

00:19:25.720 --> 00:19:27.430
go, "Well, you know,

00:19:27.440 --> 00:19:28.750
there's a reason why there's not very

00:19:28.760 --> 00:19:31.149
many of

00:19:31.149 --> 00:19:31.159
them."Nobody

00:19:31.159 --> 00:19:34.070
said it would be easy,

00:19:34.080 --> 00:19:36.510
but how bad do you want it?

00:19:36.520 --> 00:19:38.030
And that's why I thought about it. You

00:19:38.040 --> 00:19:39.790
know, there's only one Bill Gates.

00:19:39.800 --> 00:19:41.550
There's only one Warren Buffett. There's

00:19:41.560 --> 00:19:44.110
only one

00:19:44.120 --> 00:19:46.430
Elon Musk. I'm just

00:19:46.440 --> 00:19:47.550
talking about the wealthiest of the

00:19:47.560 --> 00:19:49.230
wealthiest.

00:19:49.240 --> 00:19:51.070
But they did something. And I'm not

00:19:51.080 --> 00:19:53.270
saying they did righteous things to get

00:19:53.280 --> 00:19:55.110
there, but I'm talking about people who

00:19:55.120 --> 00:19:58.550
contend for the greater wealth.

00:19:58.560 --> 00:20:00.910
It's a pattern. They

00:20:00.920 --> 00:20:02.350
have a different mindset. They

00:20:02.360 --> 00:20:05.070
think

00:20:05.070 --> 00:20:05.080
differently.

00:20:05.080 --> 00:20:07.310
They don't think poverty.

00:20:07.320 --> 00:20:09.590
They don't think quit. They don't think

00:20:09.600 --> 00:20:12.390
loser. They think winner.

00:20:12.390 --> 00:20:12.400
It's

00:20:12.400 --> 00:20:14.510
like when they say you could

00:20:14.520 --> 00:20:15.870
retire and never have to work again,

00:20:15.880 --> 00:20:16.990
"Elon,

00:20:17.000 --> 00:20:19.830
you're worth $500 million.

00:20:19.840 --> 00:20:20.390
You're

00:20:20.400 --> 00:20:22.150
the richest person in the world.

00:20:22.160 --> 00:20:24.750
Why do you keep

00:20:24.750 --> 00:20:24.760
working?"I

00:20:24.760 --> 00:20:26.230
was thinking,

00:20:26.240 --> 00:20:28.590
why? Why would you?

00:20:28.600 --> 00:20:30.190
You're never going to spend all that if

00:20:30.200 --> 00:20:32.390
you just had it by yourself. That's

00:20:32.400 --> 00:20:34.230
an absurd amount of money. He's

00:20:34.240 --> 00:20:36.230
almost

00:20:36.240 --> 00:20:38.310
halfway to a

00:20:38.320 --> 00:20:41.030
trillion dollars.

00:20:41.040 --> 00:20:44.030
Do you realize that's

00:20:44.030 --> 00:20:44.040
a lot

00:20:44.040 --> 00:20:46.990
money? That's rich.

00:20:47.000 --> 00:20:48.550
But yet you just have that drive to

00:20:48.560 --> 00:20:50.750
keep going.

00:20:50.760 --> 00:20:52.190
You're just built

00:20:52.200 --> 00:20:53.870
differently.

00:20:53.880 --> 00:20:55.710
What does it

00:20:55.720 --> 00:20:58.950
take to be in ministry for 50 years

00:20:58.960 --> 00:21:02.190
like my friends?

00:21:02.200 --> 00:21:04.710
Not a victim.

00:21:04.720 --> 00:21:06.550
Not somebody who's always whining about

00:21:06.560 --> 00:21:08.510
their life and about demonic attacks.

00:21:08.520 --> 00:21:10.430
That's why I checked myself.

00:21:10.440 --> 00:21:12.110
You're not a victim,

00:21:12.110 --> 00:21:12.120
Brandon.

00:21:12.120 --> 00:21:13.590
A victim's not

00:21:13.600 --> 00:21:16.510
going to make it.

00:21:16.520 --> 00:21:20.230
Whiners, don't be a whiner. Be a winner. That's

00:21:20.230 --> 00:21:20.240
what

00:21:20.240 --> 00:21:21.270
he said, Brandon. You're not going

00:21:21.280 --> 00:21:22.710
to do this and

00:21:22.720 --> 00:21:27.990
be a whiner.

00:21:28.000 --> 00:21:29.950
You're built for pressure. I said you

00:21:29.960 --> 00:21:34.350
were closers. I'm putting in my closers.

00:21:34.360 --> 00:21:36.190
So, every single one of you that are

00:21:36.200 --> 00:21:37.990
watching right now, I believe that God

00:21:38.000 --> 00:21:40.150
has called you for such a time as this.

00:21:40.160 --> 00:21:43.310
And he didn't build you to

00:21:43.320 --> 00:21:46.310
fail. He did not build you to be a

00:21:46.310 --> 00:21:46.320
whiner,

00:21:46.320 --> 00:21:47.950
but

00:21:47.950 --> 00:21:47.960
a

00:21:47.960 --> 00:21:50.830
winner.

00:21:50.840 --> 00:21:53.990
How bad do you want it in your life? I

00:21:54.000 --> 00:21:56.070
want change. And that's what I thought.

00:21:56.080 --> 00:21:57.270
All the times whenever it

00:21:57.270 --> 00:21:57.280
came

00:21:57.280 --> 00:21:59.150
down to

00:21:59.160 --> 00:22:01.470
working for minimum wage, working for

00:22:01.480 --> 00:22:03.510
barely getting by,

00:22:03.520 --> 00:22:08.990
and you work your tail end off

00:22:09.000 --> 00:22:11.270
by the sweat of your brow all day

00:22:11.280 --> 00:22:13.710
long for those eight hours a day, Monday

00:22:13.720 --> 00:22:14.990
through Friday, and you go get

00:22:15.000 --> 00:22:17.350
another job. You've got two jobs, you're

00:22:17.360 --> 00:22:18.630
working it,

00:22:18.640 --> 00:22:20.630
and you never make it. I've

00:22:20.640 --> 00:22:22.550
always read these books and I

00:22:22.560 --> 00:22:24.669
listen and I study about these people

00:22:24.679 --> 00:22:27.030
who have been successful.

00:22:27.040 --> 00:22:30.630
They have an idea

00:22:30.640 --> 00:22:34.230
to solve a problem.

